Use queueScheduler for synchronous, trampolined recursion (depth-safe). Use asapScheduler for microtask-queue dispatch (before setTimeout, after Promise). Use asyncScheduler for macrotask dispatch (setTimeout-backed). All three implement SchedulerLike.

```typescript
import { of, Observable, observeOn, asyncScheduler, asapScheduler, queueScheduler } from "rxjs";

const fromQueue$: Observable<number> = of(1).pipe(observeOn(queueScheduler));
const fromAsap$: Observable<number> = of(2).pipe(observeOn(asapScheduler));
const fromAsync$: Observable<number> = of(3).pipe(observeOn(asyncScheduler));

fromQueue$.subscribe((v: number) => { void v; });
fromAsap$.subscribe((v: number) => { void v; });
fromAsync$.subscribe((v: number) => { void v; });
```

queueScheduler schedules work synchronously using a trampoline â€” recursive schedules are flattened into a FIFO queue so you don't blow the call stack. asapScheduler schedules on the microtask queue (via Promise.resolve().then), so work runs after the current sync task but before setTimeout callbacks. Pick queue for sync depth-safe recursion; pick asap when you want as soon as possible but not sync.

