```

timestamp() attaches the absolute wall-clock time (ms since epoch) to each value, producing { value, timestamp }. timeInterval() instead attaches the relative gap (ms since the previous emission), producing { value, interval }. Use timestamp for event logging or wire protocols; use timeInterval for debugging cadence or throttle behaviour.

